Let $P$ be the point chosen at random.  The point $P$ is closer to $O$ than to any of the four vertices if and only if $P$ is on the circle centered at $O$ with radius $k$.  The area of the circle is $\pi k^2$, and the area of the rectangle is $2k \cdot 2k = 4k^2$.  The probability that $P$ is closer to $O$ than to any of the four vertices is $\frac{\pi k^2}{4k^2} = \boxed{\frac{\pi}{4}}$.  [asy]
size(200);
